title: For Sale:  IZH Baikal Drozd air pistol
postcontent:
The Drozd is made in Russia by IZH-Baikal. It uses a standard 12-gram CO2 cartridge and six AA batteries. There are three switches to operate the unique select-fire mechanism. The first one turns on the gun. The second one selects the firing mode: semi-auto (one shot with each pull of the trigger), three-round burst (full-auto) or six-round burst (full-auto). The third switch controls the burst rate: 300 rounds per minute, 450 rounds per minute or 600 rounds per minute.

 The gun comes with a detachable shoulder stock (increases length by 5.75"), scope rail, sights, one 30-round magazine and a BB loader. The magazine holds the ammo and the CO2 cartridge.

 The above I copied off this link.
http://www.pyramydair.com/s/m/IZH_Drozd_BB_Pistol/362#Description

title: For Sale:  LaserMax Guide Rod Laser, Springfield XDM9/40
postcontent:
The LaserMax guide rod laser sights gives you the additional convenience of a laser sight with not external additions to your weapon. Unlike all other laser sights, the guide rod laser is completely internal and simply replaces the factory guide rod and take down lever. With the guide rod sighting system there is no need to replace holsters, remove tactical lights or grips because the laser sight fits right into your current setup with no gunsmithing required.

Not only are these units convenient, but they are reliable and built with high quality material and Wolff Gunsprings, so you know your getting the best there is. LaserMax guide rod laser have been torture tested to Military and Homeland Security Specs including:
Blowing sand tests
Salt water corrosion test
5 story drop to concrete
Extreme tempetures
2 hour salt water submersion at 66 feet
20,000 round live-fire test

When you want the added confidence of a pulsating red laser sight, the LaserMax guide rod lasers will provide exactly that. On the flipside, when you do not want to give away your position or just do not want the laser at the time, the guide rod lasers are not in the way and are easily deactivated for both right and left handed shooters.

postcontent:
This is a brand new in box CMMG M4 AR-15 semi-automatic rifle chambered for 5.56mm NATO. This rifle features a 16" 4140 Chrome Moly Steel M4 profile barrel with a 1:9" twist rate suitable for most commerical ammunition. This barrel boasts CMMG's W.A.S.P. salt bath nitrocarbuerization treatment, sometimes known as nitriding, which offers improved wear, abrasion, and corrosion resistance as compared to chrome lining or phosphating. Unlike chrome lining, where the chrome is built up on the surface, nitriding converts the surface without build-up, so accuracy is not compromised. The barrel and upper receiver have M4 feed ramps for flawless cycling. A "F" marked front sight post/gas block is fitted, and a removable MBUS rear sight is included.

The upper receiver is forged aluminum with a flat top Picatinny rail for easy and secure mounting of optics. This particular rifle has a quad rail handguard installed, making mounting accessories like tactical lights, fore grips, and bipods, among others, quick and easy. The lower is forged as well, with a low shelf for RDIAS, and is compatible with standard mil-spec componentry. The magazine well is bevelled for quicker, more confident reloads. An adjustable butt stock and A2-style pistol grip are outfitted. Front and rear sling mounts are mounted for easy carrying.

One 30 round PMAG is included.

I will be at the Topeka show this weekend  both days. 


The HK Law Enforcement Modification (LEM) trigger system combines the advantages of a cocked striker component (constant level of trigger pull from first to last round fired) with a double-action hammer system. Using such an enhanced trigger system consolidates ease of use and safety into a convenient, innovative trigger operation—one that reduces the chance of unintended firing. And in case of an ammunition-related failure to fire, all that is needed is an additional second or third squeeze of the trigger without the need of first pulling the slide back to re-cock the pistol. The enhanced LEM trigger system combines the reliability of a double action revolver trigger with the crisp trigger of a single action pistol.

I know it's not a new 1100$ pistol any more as I have fired 20 rnds through it.  Perry Ks
